						Link to application form >
					</button>
				</a>
				<h2>Overview:</h2>

				<p>
					We are looking for student volunteers to help with the
					organisation of INTERACT 2023!
					<br /><br />
					Student volunteers (SVs) are an essential part of our conference.
					You will be involved in a number of different structural and
					organisational tasks to help ensure the conference runs smoothly
					and is a fun experience for all.
					<br /><br />
					Being an SV will allow you to attend the conference free of charge
					and give you the opportunity to work and network with HCI researchers
					and academics from around the world. For those not familiar with
					how a conference runs, this is a great opportunity to get involved
					and see how things are run from the inside. (It also looks great
					on the CV!)
					<br /><br />
					SVs will be expected to be available for the whole conference
					period plus an orientation and training session. We do not expect
					you to work the whole day, and you are free to attend the talks
					and other activities at the conference when you are not required
					to work. More information on eligibility and what to expect can
					be found below.
					<br /><br />
					If you are interested in being a student volunteer, please fill
					out this application form. We look forward to working with you!
					Please feel free to email us if you have any questions.
					<br /><br />
					Sanjit Samaddar (sanjit.samaddar@york.ac.uk) and Daniel Lock
					(daniel.lock@york.ac.uk)
					<br />
					Student Volunteer Co-Chairs, INTERACT 2023
				</p>

				<h2>Eligibility:</h2>

				<p>
					To become a student volunteer, you must have had student
					status for at least one semester during the academic year
					2022/23. We are more than happy to accept undergraduate,
					graduate, and PhD students and we welcome applications from
					both experienced and new student volunteers.
				</p>

				<h2>What we expect from you:</h2>

				<ul>
					<li>
						Attend the conference for 3 days (30th August - 1st
						September) OR 5 days (28th August - 1st September)
					</li>
					<li>
						Attend an induction session on 27th August (SV for 5
						days) or 29th August (SV for 3 days)
					</li>
					<li>Work approximately 5 hours a day</li>
					<li>Be on time to tasks</li>
					<li>
						Communicate with fellow SVs and SV chairs as required.
					</li>
					<li>
						Tasks will include but are not limited to:
						<ul>
							<li>Helping at the check in desk</li>
							<li>Monitoring sessions</li>
							<li>
								Providing help and direction to conference
								attendees
							</li>
							<li>Facilitating Q/A at sessions</li>
							<li>Helping setup demos and workshops</li>
							<li>Helping with audio-visual equipment</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>What you can expect from us:</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Registration fees covered by the conference</li>
					<li>Food, Tea/Coffee provided by the conference</li>
					<li>Time to interact with fellow attendees and SVs</li>
					<li>Orientation and SV training provided</li>
					<li>
						Please note: The conference cannot cover travel and
						accommodation costs for SVs. However, a limited number
						of rooms are available on campus that can be allocated
						to SVs. Please indicate if and why you may need a room
						on campus. These are likely to be prioritised for SVs
						joining us from outside the UK.
					</li>
				</ul>

				

				
			</section>

			<section class="sv-content-2">
				<h2>How to apply:</h2>
				<p>
					Please fill out <a class="underline" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeiR0tHRBTaTT2urpprC4Y7obfKeXKlVJIa0euaeHPlte8Lyg/viewform">this form</a> (or from the button below) to apply to be a student volunteer. Please answer the form’s
					questions in detail. 
					<br><br>
					Note that we won’t be using a lottery system but use the form’s answers
					to anonymously select the best-fitting volunteers.
					<br><br>
					Applications are open until <b>03/07/2023 (23:59, Anywhere on Earth)</b> and we will aim to be in
					touch by 14/07/2023.
				</p>
				<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeiR0tHRBTaTT2urpprC4Y7obfKeXKlVJIa0euaeHPlte8Lyg/viewform">
					<button>
						Apply to be a SV >
					</button>
				</a>
			</section>
